               Where chiefeſt pleaſure hath hir biding place,
               Where ioye ſurinounts, where griefe can not anoye,
               Where liues the king of euerlaſting grace,
               That well rewardes eche minde that doth employe
               Them ſelfe in trauaile to attaine that place:
               And doth condemne to euerlaſting paine,
               All thoſe that him forſake for pleaſures vaine.
            
            
