               Whoſe ſtately tops doe ſeeme to touch the ſkies,
               The baſes ſquare are framed faire below,
               With ſuch proportions as pleaſeth beſt the eies,
               In order placed, and ſtanding row by row,
               Adourned braue with torches flaming bright,
               That ſeeme to ſpoyle the day it ſelfe of light.
            
            
