                  ſt alwayes in thy breſt,
               Take heede that none be placed him aboue,
               Eſteeme no creature ſo aboue the reſt,
               That loue thereof ſhall him from thee remoue,
               For that beſide is foule Idolatrie,
               To loue a worldly thing exceſſiuclie.
            
            
               Not only Imageſeruers haue the name,
               Of blinde Idolatours, but euerie ſuch▪
               
               That inwardly with feruent loue doth flame,
